news.title: UD minister directs Hyderabad civic body to speed up 2-BHK house distribution
news.para: ​​At a review meeting held at Hyderabad Growth Corridor Limited office in Nanakramguda on Monday, KTR told officials to prepare guidelines for distribution of 60,000 2BHK houses that have been completed.

news.title: Morbi ceramic units to cut production for a month
news.para: Morbi’s yearly turnover is Rs 50,000 crore and yearly export is about Rs 15,000 crore. The only biggest competitor of Morbi in the world is China.

news.title: Chandigarh administration asks departments to submit details of recent auctions
news.para: Departments were asked to provide details like number of properties put up for auction; list of properties auctioned and list of properties which did not find any takers.

news.title: Soon, assess your property tax with new software in Lucknow
news.para: As of now, people have to fill a self-assessment form that is scrutinised by the taxation officer of the area and the tax amount is generated.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to rent out vacant 15-storey office tower
news.para: However, local residents said that instead of a private company or a bank, the Authority should rent out the tower to a government department.

news.title: 'Aravalis' not in new draft NCR 2041 plan, Haryana wanted 'hills' gone too
news.para: ​​The draft plan eventually put in public domain contained the terms “mountains and hills” to determine what constitutes a “natural zone”.

news.title: Shree Cement to invest Rs 2,500 crore to set up manufacturing plant in Guntur
news.para: ​​The company has decided to invest nearly 2,500 crore. Shree Cement's board has approved the plans to set up the new plant.

news.title: SC very unhappy with mechanical orders of NGT
news.para: With a growing number of cases related to environment and pollution clogging the high courts, the NGT was created with exclusive jurisdiction over such matters and to relieve the load on the HCs.

news.title: China: Shimao Group misses repayment on $1 billion bond
news.para: The non-repayment was the first missed public offshore payment for the Shanghai-based developer. With an outstanding $6.1 billion international bonds, Shimao is the sixth largest issuer among Chinese developers, according to Refinitiv.

news.title: ED attaches properties worth Rs 136 crore of Dreamz Infra India, directors in Bengaluru
news.para: ​​The assets are held in the name of Dreamz Infra India Limited, its managing director (MD) Disha Choudhary, TGS Constructions Private Limited, its MD Mandeep Kaur and others.

news.title: UDH to impose fees on violators of buildings bylaws in Rajasthan
news.para: After receiving directions from UDH minister Shanti Dhariwal in a recent meeting, the UDH and local self-government (LSG) department will soon issue orders for development authorities, and other urban local bodies.

news.title: Evergrande canvassing creditors' support against winding-up petition: Source
news.para: Evergrande, which is deemed to be in default on its nearly $23 billion of offshore debt and is working on a debt restructuring plan, aims to submit the backing of creditors as part of the evidence to the court ahead of the first hearing on the winding-up petition on Aug. 31, the person said.

news.title: Prayagraj: Number of registries jump manifold two years after pandemic
news.para: In the nine assistant registrar offices of the district, in comparison to 1,960 registries done in May 2021, 5,513 registries have been done in May this year.

news.title: 315Work Avenue lease out over 70,000 sq ft to TeamLease in Bengaluru
news.para: The company also plans to add another 1.5 million sq ft office space over a period of next 1 year and will add few more cities in the near future.

news.title: Bombay HC orders slum dwellers to vacate from plot marked for Metro Line 6
news.para: The HC dismissed a petition filed in 2019 by slum dwellers who sought directions to Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority [MMRDA] to determine whether its hutments were on land earmarked for construction of the Metro 6 line.
